block.create.railway_casing.tooltip.summ: Press the _open csille menu_ key (default _alt_) to select the _bogey style_ to place.
block.create.track_station.tooltip.summa: A _deployer_ holding a _wrench_ can automatically assemble and disassemble trains by hitting a _station_. _hint_: hoppers can be used to put a wrench in a deployer.
block.railways.boiler.tooltip.summary: _wrench_ the face of kazán to change it to a _smokebox door_, sneak while placing to _raise_ the kazán up _half_ a blokk.
block.railways.buffer.tooltip.summary: Can be dyed by _clicking_ with dye.
block.railways.generic_radial.tooltip.su: Press and hold the _open cycle menu_ key (default _alt_) to select variants of this blokk.
block.railways.handcar.summary: Use a wrench to pick up.
block.railways.headstock.tooltip.summary: Press and hold the _open cycle menu_ key (default _alt_) to select variants of this blokk. Can be dyed by _clicking_ with dye.
block.railways.headstock_wood.tooltip.su: Press and hold the _open cycle menu_ key (default _alt_) to select variants of this blokk. Can be dyed by _clicking_ with dye. Wood backboard can be changed by _clicking_ with planks.
block.railways.narrow_double_scotch_boge: Keskeny gauge dupla scotch yoke csille
block.railways.smokestack.tooltip.behavi: The _emitted smoke_ will change to _soul smoke_
block.railways.smokestack.tooltip.condit: When you use a dye item on a kémény
When you use lélekhomok or lélektalaj on a kémény
block.railways.smokestack.tooltip.summar: Press and hold the _focus schematic overlay_ key (default _alt_) to select variants of this blokk.
block.railways.track_buffer.tooltip.summ: _variant_ can be changed by _wrenching the front face_, can be dyed by _clicking_ with dye and the wood board can be changed by _clicking_ with planks.
block.railways.track_phantom.summary: _phantom tracks_ are compatible with _all_ csille types
block.railways.track_phantom.tooltip.beh: _phantom tracks_ in the world will be _visible_
_phantom tracks_ in the world will be _invisible_
block.railways.track_phantom.tooltip.con: When you hold a fantom track in your hand
When you don't hold a fantom track in your hand
block.railways.track_tfc_douglas_fir_nar: Keskeny douglas erdei fenyő vasúti sín
block.railways.track_tfc_douglas_fir_wid: Széles douglas erdei fenyő vasúti sín

Incomplete széles douglas erdei fenyő track
railways.buffer.invalid_shape: Buffers must be placed on a straight track
railways.gui.bogey_menu.title: Csille preview
railways.ponder.conductor_constructing.t: Conductors are constructed with an andezit casing.
railways.ponder.conductor_redstoning.tex: Conductors can press buttons when a player looks at them.
Conductors also toggle levers when a player looks at them.
Conductors do not activate redstone if a player is wearing a different-colored cap from them.
railways.ponder.conductor_toolboxing.tex: Toolboxes function normally when equipped on conductors.
railways.ponder.door_modes.text_1: Ajtók have multiple modes of operation: normal, manual, and special
railways.ponder.door_modes.text_2: In normal mode (the default) and manual mode, manual operation of the ajtó is possible
railways.ponder.door_modes.text_3: And redstone operation works in normal mode and special mode
railways.ponder.door_modes.text_4: Ajtók in normal and special modes open and close when a contraption moves or stops
railways.ponder.door_modes.text_5: Ajtók in manual mode only change when a player interacts with them
railways.ponder.door_modes.text_6: Ajtók in special mode cannot be toggled simply by using them
railways.ponder.door_modes.text_7: Sneaking, however, allows the player to toggle the ajtó anyway
railways.ponder.train_coupler.text_1: Select a vasúti sín then place the kapcsoló nearby
railways.ponder.train_coupler.text_2: The vonat kapcsoló lets you couple and decouple trains without disassembling them
railways.ponder.train_coupler.text_3: By scrolling with a wrench you can change the gap between the couple/decouple pads
railways.ponder.train_coupler.text_4: By using a wrench you can cycle between coupling, decoupling, and both modes
railways.ponder.train_coupler.text_5: Stations can be used to help align trains for coupling
railways.ponder.train_coupler.text_6: By powering a kapcsoló you can couple/decouple a properly aligned vonat
railways.ponder.train_semaphore.text_1: Semaphores are placed on poles above vonat signals
railways.ponder.train_semaphore.text_2: Szemafor poles can be made of different materials
railways.ponder.train_semaphore.text_3: Semaphores show the current state of the signal below the pole
railways.ponder.train_semaphore.text_4: If a sárgaréz signal has multiple valid exit paths...
railways.ponder.train_semaphore.text_5: ... A second szemafor can be placed above the first
railways.ponder.train_semaphore.text_6: The bottom szemafor will now close if any of the available paths are blocked
railways.ponder.train_semaphore.text_7: The top szemafor will close if all paths are blocked
railways.ponder.train_semaphore.text_8: When 2 semaphores are placed on a non-sárgaréz signal, they both close simultaneously
railways.ponder.train_switch.text_1: Select a vasúti sín then place the switch nearby
railways.ponder.train_switch.text_2: The switch will direct any trains passing over the marker
railways.ponder.train_switch.text_3: Cycle the switch to the right by using it
railways.ponder.train_switch.text_4: Cycle the switch to the left by using it while sneaking
railways.ponder.train_switch.text_5: Switches provide a redstone-komparátor signal based on the direction: 1 for left, 0 for straight, and 2 for right
railways.ponder.train_switch.text_6: Switch direction can also be set by a redstone signal, and can be locked by powering the bottom
railways.ponder.train_switch.text_7: Projectiles also cycle switches on impact
railways.remote_lens.tool.bound_usage: Use to spy through the eyes of the bound conductor!
railways.remote_lens.tool.not_bound: Not bound, use on a conductor wearing goggles to bind.
railways.station.train_limit.tooltip.1: Reserve station before approaching vonat has arrived
railways.station.train_limit.tooltip.2: To more evenly space trains in a multi-platform station
railways.tooltip.coupler.error.carriage_: Carriage(s) not aligned properly. Hint: the center of the csille should be aligned over the kapcsoló track point.
Carriages must be facing the same direction. Hint: use a wrench to reorient the carriages.
railways.tooltip.coupler.error.missing_t: Requires both track points to be occupied
railways.tooltip.coupler.error.mode_not_: Action not permitted in current mode
railways.whistle.failure.conductor_missi: Conductor not found or it was not riding the bound vonat.
railways.whistle.failure.not_owner: You must be the owner of the vonat to cancel its schedule.
railways.whistle.not_owner: You must be the owner of the vonat to bind the whistle.
railways.whistle.tool.bound_auto_clear: Or on levegő to dismiss the auto schedule of the bound vonat
railways.whistle.tool.bound_auto_usage: Deployers can use whistles on stations to summon trains
railways.whistle.tool.bound_usage: Use on a track or station to summon the bound vonat!
railways.whistle.tool.not_bound: Not bound, use on a conductor riding a vonat to bind.
